-- limb (h) needs BOTH conjuncts: feature present AND not needed.
`claim via (h) — features needed` MEANS Ground5FClaim WITH
  `dwelling-house was supported accommodation when the tenancy was granted`  IS TRUE
  `dwelling-house is managed accommodation`                                  IS FALSE
  `relevant date`                                                            IS `relevant date 2025`
  `tenancy granted to provide support services for a limited time to enable the tenant to live in other accommodation in the future`  IS FALSE
  `the period for which those support services were to be provided has ended`  IS FALSE
  `a person other than the landlord provides or provided support services to the tenant`  IS FALSE
  `the support services have come to an end`                                  IS FALSE
  `the person is not fulfilling their obligations for the provision of those services`  IS FALSE
  `(b) landlord used reasonable endeavours to find another provider but was not able to`  IS FALSE
  `the accommodation or support services were funded wholly or partly by someone other than the landlord or the tenant`  IS FALSE
  `that funding is no longer being provided`                                 IS FALSE
  `(c) landlord used reasonable endeavours to identify alternative funding but was not able to`  IS FALSE
  `(c) date the landlord made reasonable endeavours to identify alternative funding`  IS `endeavour before relevant date`
  `it would not be reasonable for the landlord to continue to provide accommodation or for the provider to continue`  IS FALSE
  `the financial viability of the landlord or of supported accommodation provided to others would be threatened if the landlord continued to provide or fund a supported accommodation project of which the tenant's dwelling-house forms part`  IS FALSE
  `(d) landlord used reasonable endeavours to identify alternative funding for the project but was not able to`  IS FALSE
  `(d) date the landlord made reasonable endeavours to identify alternative funding for the project`  IS `endeavour before relevant date`
  `the tenant does not need the level of support services that are provided`  IS FALSE
  `the tenant does not need any support services`                            IS FALSE
  `the support services that are provided do not meet the tenant's needs`     IS FALSE
  `the dwelling-house has physical features intended to enable persons with needs for particular support services to live more independently`  IS TRUE
  `those physical features are not needed by the tenant`                      IS FALSE
  `the dwelling-house is physically unsuitable for a person with the tenant's needs for support services to live in`  IS FALSE

#ASSERT NOT `(h) — physical features present but not needed by the tenant` `claim via (h) — features needed`

§§ `Limb (i) made out — dwelling-house physically unsuitable for the tenant's needs`

`claim via (i)` MEANS Ground5FClaim WITH
  `dwelling-house was supported accommodation when the tenancy was granted`  IS TRUE
  `dwelling-house is managed accommodation`                                  IS FALSE
  `relevant date`                                                            IS `relevant date 2025`
  `tenancy granted to provide support services for a limited time to enable the tenant to live in other accommodation in the future`  IS FALSE
  `the period for which those support services were to be provided has ended`  IS FALSE
  `a person other than the landlord provides or provided support services to the tenant`  IS FALSE
  `the support services have come to an end`                                  IS FALSE
  `the person is not fulfilling their obligations for the provision of those services`  IS FALSE
  `(b) landlord used reasonable endeavours to find another provider but was not able to`  IS FALSE
  `the accommodation or support services were funded wholly or partly by someone other than the landlord or the tenant`  IS FALSE
  `that funding is no longer being provided`                                 IS FALSE
  `(c) landlord used reasonable endeavours to identify alternative funding but was not able to`  IS FALSE
  `(c) date the landlord made reasonable endeavours to identify alternative funding`  IS `endeavour before relevant date`
  `it would not be reasonable for the landlord to continue to provide accommodation or for the provider to continue`  IS FALSE
  `the financial viability of the landlord or of supported accommodation provided to others would be threatened if the landlord continued to provide or fund a supported accommodation project of which the tenant's dwelling-house forms part`  IS FALSE
  `(d) landlord used reasonable endeavours to identify alternative funding for the project but was not able to`  IS FALSE
  `(d) date the landlord made reasonable endeavours to identify alternative funding for the project`  IS `endeavour before relevant date`
  `the tenant does not need the level of support services that are provided`  IS FALSE
  `the tenant does not need any support services`                            IS FALSE
  `the support services that are provided do not meet the tenant's needs`     IS FALSE
  `the dwelling-house has physical features intended to enable persons with needs for particular support services to live more independently`  IS FALSE
  `those physical features are not needed by the tenant`                      IS FALSE
  `the dwelling-house is physically unsuitable for a person with the tenant's needs for support services to live in`  IS TRUE

#ASSERT `(i) — dwelling-house physically unsuitable for the tenant's needs` `claim via (i)`
#ASSERT `Ground 5F made out`                                               `claim via (i)`

§§ `Gateway knocked out — NOT supported accommodation when granted, though limb (a) applies`

-- The gateway is a hard precondition: if the dwelling-house was not supported
-- accommodation when the tenancy was granted, the ground is not made out even
-- though limb (a) (and any other) would otherwise apply.
`claim — gateway fails but (a) applies` MEANS Ground5FClaim WITH
  `dwelling-house was supported accommodation when the tenancy was granted`  IS FALSE
  `dwelling-house is managed accommodation`                                  IS FALSE
  `relevant date`                                                            IS `relevant date 2025`
  `tenancy granted to provide support services for a limited time to enable the tenant to live in other accommodation in the future`  IS TRUE
  `the period for which those support services were to be provided has ended`  IS TRUE
  `a person other than the landlord provides or provided support services to the tenant`  IS FALSE
  `the support services have come to an end`                                  IS FALSE
  `the person is not fulfilling their obligations for the provision of those services`  IS FALSE
  `(b) landlord used reasonable endeavours to find another provider but was not able to`  IS FALSE
  `the accommodation or support services were funded wholly or partly by someone other than the landlord or the tenant`  IS FALSE
  `that funding is no longer being provided`                                 IS FALSE
  `(c) landlord used reasonable endeavours to identify alternative funding but was not able to`  IS FALSE
  `(c) date the landlord made reasonable endeavours to identify alternative funding`  IS `endeavour before relevant date`
  `it would not be reasonable for the landlord to continue to provide accommodation or for the provider to continue`  IS FALSE
  `the financial viability of the landlord or of supported accommodation provided to others would be threatened if the landlord continued to provide or fund a supported accommodation project of which the tenant's dwelling-house forms part`  IS FALSE
  `(d) landlord used reasonable endeavours to identify alternative funding for the project but was not able to`  IS FALSE
  `(d) date the landlord made reasonable endeavours to identify alternative funding for the project`  IS `endeavour before relevant date`
  `the tenant does not need the level of support services that are provided`  IS FALSE
  `the tenant does not need any support services`                            IS FALSE
  `the support services that are provided do not meet the tenant's needs`     IS FALSE
  `the dwelling-house has physical features intended to enable persons with needs for particular support services to live more independently`  IS FALSE
  `those physical features are not needed by the tenant`                      IS FALSE
  `the dwelling-house is physically unsuitable for a person with the tenant's needs for support services to live in`  IS FALSE

#ASSERT     `any of (a)-(i) applies` `claim — gateway fails but (a) applies`
#ASSERT NOT `Ground 5F made out`     `claim — gateway fails but (a) applies`
